---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProjectCard from '../components/ProjectCard.astro';
import { getEntry } from 'astro:content';

const copilot = await getEntry('projects', 'mortgage-readiness-copilot');
---
<BaseLayout pageTitle="About — Jiri Sindelar" description="About Jiri Sindelar — software engineer, builder, learner.">

  <section class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 items-start">
    <img
      src="/jirka-photo.png"
      alt="Jiri Sindelar"
      class="w-48 h-48 sm:w-56 sm:h-56 rounded-xl object-cover shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Jiri Sindelar</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Deep in flow, exploring new ideas emerging in software.
        Lately, I’ve been digging into Open Banking and building an agentic app.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The story</h2>
    <p>
      Coming in the office, checking JIRA, standup, coding, consulting, planning... peaceful ordinary day in ordinary developer's life, 
      full of jokes and smile with my dear colleagues. But something was brewing.
      </p>
      <p>
      I had great years in Prague's banking - working on Java backends, 
      surrounded by brilliant people who'd built software around the world, understanding the whole business around.
      I learned a lot from them. But in my thoughts it was like: 
      "Hmm.. being able to invent things to people in every corner of the world who would never have imagined that such a thing could exist. 
      It's so cool... damn!" 
      So I decided to take a leap and fill my gaps in English in San Diego, London and Melbourne which took more than a year. 
      </p>
      <p>
      Currently, I'm back and looking forward to jump back into the industry.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What I'm into now</h2>
    <p>
      Here's what I'm exploring right now — came out of an idea that mortgage
      assessment is still user unfriendly, if you have multiple accounts it's time-consuming and annoying activity,
      Open Banking gives the access to client's financial data can make it easier:
    </p>
    {copilot && (
      <ProjectCard
        slug={copilot.id}
        title={copilot.data.title}
        description={copilot.data.description}
        tags={copilot.data.tags}
        sourceUrl={copilot.data.sourceUrl}
        liveUrl={copilot.data.liveUrl}
      />
    )}
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">What I'm open to</h2>
    <p>
      If you're into Open Banking, agentic design, or product development, let's chat:
      <a href="mailto:jirkasindelar323@gmail.com" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">email me</a>
      or find me on
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jiri-sindelar-540a5b143" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline">LinkedIn</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Outside of code</h2>
    <p>
      Improv, history, volunteering, and nature.
    </p>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
